                            <comment id="488474" author="adilger" created="Fri, 20 Feb 2026 20:52:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, this ticket has too much &quot;wrong&quot; detail to repurpose, I will open a new ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="488473" author="adilger" created="Fri, 20 Feb 2026 20:50:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We still want to do this, by importing the ISA-L assembly-optimized versions into Lustre, instead of re-implementing them ourselves.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ISA-L assembly code can be used immediately from &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend/resync&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, and eventually from the kernel (with proper save/restore of the FP/AVX/SSE registers and handling of NASM code).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468519" author="paf0186" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2025 19:56:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should just use the optimized versions available in ISL instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="458385" author="adilger" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2025 09:06:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We shouldn&apos;t be optimizing the EC calculations yet, for two reasons:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;we don&apos;t have working code yet, so faster both working code doesn&apos;t help us&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;there is optimized ASM code for x86 and ARM CPUs in the BSD ISA-L library, we just haven&apos;t included them into the code yet, because the C implementation was more portable and sufficient during development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
